%N A394077 Largest dihedral angle, in radians, in an uniform heptagonal antiprism.
%C A394077 This is the dihedral angle between triangular faces.
%H A394077 Paolo Xausa, <a href="/A394077/b394077.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A394077 David I. McCooey, <a href="https://dmccooey.com/polyhedra/HeptagonalAntiprism.html">Heptagonal Antiprism</a>.
%H A394077 Polytope Wiki, <a href="https://polytope.miraheze.org/wiki/Heptagonal_antiprism">Heptagonal antiprism</a>.
%H A394077 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/Antiprism.html">Antiprism</a>.
%H A394077 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Antiprism">Antiprism</a>.
%F A394077 Equals arccos((1 - 4*cos(Pi/7))/3) = arccos((1 - 4*A073052)/3).
%F A394077 Equals arccos(c), where c = -0.867958... is the smallest root of 27*x^3 - 9*x^2 - 27*x + 1.
%e A394077 2.621873093429493958578568422819526896777753859808...
%t A394077 First[RealDigits[ArcCos[(1 - 4*Cos[Pi/7])/3], 10, 100]] (* or *)
%t A394077 First[RealDigits[Max[PolyhedronData["HeptagonalAntiprism", "DihedralAngles"]], 10, 100]]
%Y A394077 Cf. A394076 (the other dihedral angle).
%Y A394077 Cf. A394071 (volume), A394072 (surface area), A394073 (midradius), A394074 (circumradius), A394075 (height).
